    "attributes": {
        "action": "Lower Maths GCSE grade requirement for arts teacher training courses.",
        "additional_details": "Maths is not directly relevant to arts subjects and the higher grade requirement could be stopping educated, talented and experienced people becoming teachers. Some people with dyslexia and dyscalculia could be turned away because they don't have the higher maths grade.\r\n \r\nI would like the Government to lower the Maths GCSE requirement grade for creative subjects such as Art, Drama and Music.\r\n",
        "background": "Currently the maths entry requirement into teacher training courses for arts subjects is a GCSE level 4 or above. We believe this should be lowered to level 1 or above. ",
